  "abstract": {
    "value": "The reaction of γ-stannylated propargyl esters in the presence of a cationic gold(I) catalyst affords vinylidenecyclopropane derivatives as a mixture of diastereomers. The cis-geometry of the alkenes is almost entirely retained in the product. DFT calculations suggest the involvement of the gold(I)-stabilized propargyl cation as a resonance form of gold(I)-coordinated allenylidene species.",
    "source": "llm_from_front_matter",
